GENIA-MedCo coreference corpus version 1.0

- It contains coreference annotation made to the GENIA corpus.

- The GENIA corpus consists of 1,999 PubMed abstracts which were collected
  using three MeSH terms: Human, Blood Cells, and Transcription Factors.

- The coreference annotation was produced by Information Extraction and Text
  Mining Group at Institute for Infocomm Research (I2R) through MedCo
  Annotation Project.

- The format conversion into GENIA format, and minor bug fixes were made by
  the GENIA team.


History

Sep 29, 2010	Initial version (v.1.0) released.


References

GENIA project: http://www-tsujii.is.s.u-tokyo.ac.jp/GENIA/
MedCo Annotation Project: http://nlp.i2r.a-star.edu.sg/medco.html
